    "body": "As for now the `ShallowWaterModel` is implemented in a conservative form. \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://render.githubusercontent.com/render/math?math={\\partial_t(uh)%2B\\partial_x(hu^2%2B\\frac{1}{2}gh^2)%2B\\partial_y(huv)-fvh=0}\">\r\n<img src=\"https://render.githubusercontent.com/render/math?math={\\partial_t(vh)%2B\\partial_x(huv)%2B\\partial_y(hv^2%2B\\frac{1}{2}gh^2)%2Bfuh=0}\">\r\n<img src=\"https://render.githubusercontent.com/render/math?math={\\partial_th%2B\\partial_x(hu)%2B\\partial_y(hv)=0}\">\r\n\r\nThis PR attempts to introduce a non-conservative form of the equation with a vector invariant formulation of advection\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://render.githubusercontent.com/render/math?math={\\partial_tu-(\\zeta%2Bf)v%2B\\partial_x(gh%2Bk)=0}\">\r\n<img src=\"https://render.githubusercontent.com/render/math?math={\\partial_tv%2B(\\zeta%2Bf)u%2B\\partial_y(gh%2Bk)=0}\">\r\n<img src=\"https://render.githubusercontent.com/render/math?math={\\partial_th%2B\\partial_x(hu)%2B\\partial_y(hv)=0}\">\r\n\r\nsuch that we can treat the advection with high order WENO reconstruction.\r\nWe should also think about introducing bathymetric terms (<img src=\"https://render.githubusercontent.com/render/math?math={gh\\partial_x h_B}\">  and  <img src=\"https://render.githubusercontent.com/render/math?math={gh\\partial_y h_B}\">) and viscous term (#2403)\r\n\r\nwith @francispoulin ",
